  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "If an user adds an `url` field to the Hardhat Network config, we don't detect it during the config validation, but rather leave it there.\r\n\r\nThen, when we initialize the network provider, Hardhat gets confused and treats it as an HTTP network config.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis should help reproduce it:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nnetworks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      url: \"valid node url\",\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n```",
